submission.name: IMG_1628.jpeg
submission.description:
With Alterro having two omni-gems and their power in his possession, the Mane 6 and their friends know that both Skyros and Equestria are in danger, so like they did just a year prior with Allura, they gather Equestria‚Äôs finest forces, as well as the forces of the dragons from the Isle of Scaly, to try and keep updated with King Andros, Queen Mariam and their alicorn forces on Skyros‚Äô slow descent while trying to protect Equestria from Alterro‚Äôs impending invasion, including keeping the Unity Crystals protected. However, the Unity Crystals have other plans, and send the Mane 6 on another Unity Quest, with their families and friends promising to keep the realm safe until their return.

> 
> 
Our heroes soon arrive in London in 1940, the time of the Blitz, where they meet the four Pevensie siblings-- Peter, Susan, Edmund and Lucy-- and their four feline friends-- Ginny, Buddy, Sparks and Bitsy-- who are evacuated to the countryside and sent to the country home of Professor Digory Kirke until it is safe to return to London‚Ä¶ but who knows when that might be.

> 
> 
However, during a game of hide-and-seek, the Mane 6 and their friends discover the hidden world of Narnia, which is accessed through a magical wardrobe in the estate. It is soon learned that the White Witch has turned Narnia into a world of eternal winter, and has accepted Alterro as her royal advisor, while the Pevensie children are dubbed part of a prophecy to bring the White Witch down.

> 
> 
Now with the stake of not just one, not two, but three worlds on their shoulders, the Mane 6 know that defeating the White Witch and Alterro, as well as protecting all of the Pevensie children, is not going to be easy. But, aided by the magnificent lion Aslan, a Narnian Wild Cat cub named Willa and some of the ponies‚Äô friends and family members from home, the Pevensies and the Mane 6 lead Narnia into a climactic battle to be set free of its endless winter and defeat Alterro and the White Witch once and for all!

submission.description:
*"Well Curi, if you were so eager to relax with one half of Twintails' gift for us, it's only fair I teat us both with the other half~ He's sure that gas of his will take quite a long time to work through the foam, so we'll be in for a good few hours of you being so adorably floaty while it does~"*

It's hearth's warming time once again, and as I make the rounds dropping off gifts here 'n' there, it's only natural that some might open them a little early. The combo of a nice big soft balloon and a small canister of P-235 is a pretty reliable mix, and while Curi might not've had much she could do with the canister, well, few can resist filling up and flopping on some squeaky soft rubber~ Thankfully, Tai and his silly little darts were quite readily compatible with the small canister of gas, and with his volunteer already waiting, all it took was a quick poke and some sliding inbetween his new balloons~

A secret santa giftie for Tai~

submission.name: MidnightFlatComm2.png
submission.description:
Ah, the joys of telekinesis, even with a flat vantage to work from it wasn't too difficult to open the box and retrieve the contents. Getting the bellows set up was a breeze as well, mostly thanks to the prominent valve and tank that provides most of the function, and with it slipped into his muzzle, one last twist to get the tank hissing away and the bellows working themselves, pumping that swelling gas into their attached balloon unhindered, he's finally back on the way to getting into shape.

Shame about the horn being one of the things to fwhoomp up as well, making that magic use a bit hindered, but oh well - wasn't like he wanted to be able to stop those bellows anyways, right?~

Commission for Midnight Luster, part 2 of 4~

submission.name: MidnightFlatComm1.png
submission.description:
Even in the dark cold days of winter, it's always a smart move to conduct any potential potion shenanigans well out and away from places where structures remaining intact is vital to comfortable living. To that end, we find Midnight Luster out in a heavy tent that's at least saved some of the grass from the snow, but in that same time, hasn't saved him from his own inattention. A potion designed to make flattening out wrinkles in clothes works just as well for flattening out ponies when imbibed, and all the warning labels won't stop a thirsty, tired, and cold unicorn from making a mistake.

Lucky, among the stuff in the tent, a conveniently convenient implement of shenaniganery is not too far away, and with his horn still being available, well, I'm sure he can sort himself out~

Commission for Midnight Luster, part 1 of 4~
